strings.Value: "Since none of you is going hunting, let's buy some decent rations next time. I've grown sick of this muck!"

"So, instead of fresh game we'll have dry rations for lunch again? If you're all too lazy to fetch us some decent meat, at least you could follow the example of the dwarves. They add sausage and dried meat to every ration!"
"There's nothing better than a fresh meal cooked by an experienced chef."
"Oh, poor little Jubie! His mean companions won't feed him! No one understands how exceptional he is! If only he could, oh, I don't know, lift up his saggy butt and go hunting for himself!"
"Right! Wow, did you really just say something useful? Something that don't make people want to punch you in the nose! That's new!"
"Field rations sap all my inspiration. You want real poetry? Then give me real food!"
